<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-925-202  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 925 202.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Nov 27 1989 n343 p102(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Desktop color scanner arena: a study. (Technology Group assessesmarket for desktop color scanners)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An assessment by a market research firm, The Technology Group,indicates that the US market for desktop color scanners is stillin its infancy, but there are signs of steady growth.andO;Applications are currently concentrated in the creative,graphic-arts, and publishing market segments.andP;  A desktop colorscanner can digitally encode color images for three- or four-colorreproduction.andP;  Most employ 8-bit encoding in three primary colorsto achieve 24-bit pixels.andP;  Flatbed scanners look and operate muchlike black and white scanners; open-bed units employ an open flatsurface with a regular camera lens, charge-coupled device, andcompensation electronics mounted in a perpendicular tower.andO;Open-bed scanners give users more control over the focus, but theyproduce a slightly grainier image and must be carefully aligned.andO;High-quality scanners and software let users create entirely newimages.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   The Technology Group (research).andO;Topic:     ScanningColorMarket AnalysisI-O DevicesGraphics Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>